28/03/2006
SPLIT, Croatia -- A five-day military drill began on Monday (27 March) in Split, Croatia, under the US-Adriatic Charter initiative. 
The naval and land exercise includes participants from the Charter signatory countries: Albania, Croatia, Macedonia and the United States. 
Several other states are observing. 
The exercise is aimed at improving co-ordination and interoperability in halting the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction. 
(HINA - 27/03/06)
